Today is my 100th day of yoga. My entire life I used to say yoga wasn't for me, and now I can't imagine my life without it. It's taught me how to move and exercise bc I love my body not because I hate it. It's taught me to meet my limits and explore my boundaries rather than push hard into poses which cause frustration. It's taught me to love myself. It's taught me the power of breathing on and off the mat. It's given me mental and physical strength. All of this, channeled through Adriene, through this phone screen, to me. Here's to 100+ more days! üéâ

My 100th yoga practice!!!   It wasnt done in 100 days (I average 6 days a week) but to imagine I would stay with it this long is amazing!  Ive had high highs, and really low, lows. Ive experienced anger, peace, confusion, frustration, continual muscle soreness, and a sense of accomplishment. I still dont like guided meditation, the notion of a 3rd eye makes my eyes roll, I dont see myself ever flying in crow, and my heels STILL dont touch the ground in DD. But Ive learned to modify both physically and mentally when needed and every once in a while I do something I couldn't think I could. Today when you went to third eye, my namaste hands pointed skyward and launched gracefully like a rocket headed into the universe. It was sooooo satisfying for me! I dont always like practice but I always find myself drawn to come back to the mat... and that pretty much says it all. Thanks Adriene!  Cant wait to see what the next 100 days of this journey bring!

AFTER yesterday's late start and feeling exhausted after a long day of being out, today, I walked in the morning and then before 12pm, I was switched on to Day 10 of the Yoga Revolution.  

I still felt tired and I had heavy legs and felt as I was ready for a rest, but instead of resting, I was focused on doing Day 10, and taking note that there is only 3 more weeks to go.

Like always, I took the class at my own pace and it was so nice to just let the body sink into the floor and let the body relax.  Unlike yesterday, I was so relaxed through out today's session and I felt as though I was in a good place all the way through.  I concentrated on my breathing and taking breaths in through the nose and breathing out through the nose and also concentrating on posture and movement.  It was like slowly waking up and stretching instead of waking up and just getting out of bed.

At the end of the 30 minutes, I felt as though my limbs were weightless and like always, I felt light headed.  I was completely relaxed and feeling so good, compared to when I wake up in the morning and I still feel tired.  I feel as though I have gone through a message and I feel as though I am in a good place which is a good thing to know.

Thank you Adriene for this challenge as I wake up each day, knowing that I have you to coach me through 30 minutes of movement and where  I am taking the time for me.

I'm redoing Revolution, as I fell into a huge rut. I had a big job opportunity that I took, and before I travelled for it I almost couldn't face doing it.
